Package: EmpiricalRate
Title: Empirical Estimation of Event Rates and Rate Ratios for Count Data
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Jiren", "Sun", email = "jiren.sun@lilly.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Linda", "Amoafo", email = "linda.amoafo@lilly.com",
           role = "aut"),
    person("Yongming", "Qu", email = "qu_yongming@lilly.com",
           role = "aut"),
    person("Eli Lilly and Company", role = c("cph", "fnd")))
Description: An empirical, distribution-free method for comparing marginal
    event rates between treatment groups in clinical trials with count
    (recurrent-event) endpoints such as hypoglycemia. Individual event
    counts are transformed to subject-level rate quantities by dividing by
    the arm-specific mean exposure, and a linear working model (ANOVA,
    ANCOVA, or the heterogeneous-covariance extension ANHECOVA) is fitted
    with robust variance estimation via the 'RobinCar' package. Marginal
    rates are back-transformed to the log-rate scale and rate ratios with
    confidence intervals are obtained by the delta method. The method
    targets the same marginal estimand as negative binomial regression
    (the ratio of marginal event rates) but avoids likelihood-based
    estimation, which improves numerical stability when events are sparse
    and does not require correct specification of a conditional mean model.
    Methods are described in Sun, Amoafo and Qu (2026) <doi:PENDING>.
